Quem ipse neglexit pater, διο. “ Ι educate a child, whom his own father has abandoned!” Donatus on this passage takes notice of a reading which entirely changes the sense, quem ipsa neglexit, pater ; “ Shall I, father, take care of a child, whom the mother herself has abandoned? ” But the other reading is certainly the best.
